<subSubSection id="E9C66514075FFFC4101301FFFA96AA08" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" type="description">
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC4101301FFFC25AB28" blockId="39.[811,1457,1013,1198]" box="[813,957,1013,1039]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC41013061EFC66AB0B" blockId="39.[811,1457,1013,1198]" box="[813,1022,1044,1070]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC41013061EFC66AB0B" box="[813,1022,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Thoracic appendages</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC41013063EFAB1AB8B" blockId="39.[811,1457,1013,1198]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Chelate P1; P1 propodus sub-rectangular, slightly globose dorso-ventrally; inner margin strongly compressed; rounded outer margin with a slight deviation at the basis of the index; slender index; wide and inflated dactylar bulge.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC4101306DEFC57ABCB" blockId="39.[813,975,1236,1262]" box="[813,975,1236,1262]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">
<heading id="FA2B81F3075FFFC4101306DEFC57ABCB" box="[813,975,1236,1262]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" reason="8">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC4101306DEFC57ABCB" box="[813,975,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Ornamentation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC4101306FEFA96AA08" blockId="39.[813,1455,1267,1326]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">P1 propodus covered by rounded, coarse and widely spaced tubercles; inner margin with a row of spines.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9C66514075FFFC41013075EFC3DA849" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC41013075EFC36AA49" blockId="39.[811,1457,1364,1900]" box="[813,942,1364,1390]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">DISCUSSION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC410130779FC77A9A9" blockId="39.[811,1457,1364,1900]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">
This species is known by some P1 propodi. Initially included within 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC41046079EFC6FAA88" authorityName="Beurlen" authorityYear="1928" box="[888,1015,1428,1453]" class="Malacostraca" family="Decapoda (awaiting allocation)" genus="Erymastacus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC41046079EFC6FAA88" box="[888,1015,1428,1453]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Erymastacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, then moved into 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC417880799FAA8AA88" authorityName="Bell" authorityYear="1863" box="[1206,1328,1427,1453]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Phlyctisoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC417880799FAA8AA88" box="[1206,1328,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Phlyctisoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075FFFC4165D079EFCFDAAE8" author="FORSTER R." pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="61 - 175" refId="ref32323" refString="FORSTER R. 1966. - Uber die Erymiden, eine alte konservative Familie der mesozoischen Dekapoden. Palaeontographica, Abt. A, 125 (4 - 6): 61 - 175." type="journal article" year="1966">Förster 1966</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC4109D07BEFC7FAAE8" baseAuthorityName="Beurlen" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[931,999,1460,1485]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC4109D07BEFC7FAAE8" box="[931,999,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Eryma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075FFFC4172007B9FA92AAE8" author="SCHWEITZER C. E. &amp; FELDMANN R. M. &amp; GARASSINO A. &amp; KARASAWA H. &amp; SCHWEIGERT G." box="[1054,1290,1459,1485]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 222" refId="ref35549" refString="SCHWEITZER C. E., FELDMANN R. M., GARASSINO A., KARASAWA H. &amp; SCHWEIGERT G. 2010. - Systematic list of fossil decapod crustacean species. Crustaceana Monographs 10: 1 - 222. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / ej. 9789004178915. i- 222" type="journal article" year="2010">
Schweitzer 
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC417A607BEFB53AAE8" box="[1176,1227,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
), and finally to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC4101207D9FC5AAAC8" authorityName="Beurlen" authorityYear="1928" box="[812,962,1491,1517]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC4101207D9FC5AAAC8" box="[812,962,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Stenodactylina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="C54D4B6E075FFFC410CE07D9FB41AAC8" author="DEVILLEZ J. &amp; CHARBONNIER S. &amp; HYZNY M. &amp; LEROY L." box="[1008,1241,1491,1517]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" pagination="515 - 541" refId="ref31314" refString="DEVILLEZ J., CHARBONNIER S., HYZNY M. &amp; LEROY L. 2016. - Review of the Early Cretaceous erymid lobsters (Crustacea: Decapoda) from the Western Tethys. Geodiversitas 38 (4): 515 - 541. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / g 2016 n 4 a 4" type="journal article" year="2016">
Devillez 
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC4177107DEFB1DAAC8" box="[1103,1157,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
. This assignment is supported by the stronger compression of the inner margin than that of outer margin, the presence of a row of coarse tubercles on inner margin (present in most of the species of the genus), the strongly inflated dactylar bulge, and the fine basis of the index.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F075FFFC4107D0499FC3DA849" blockId="39.[811,1457,1364,1900]" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">
Because only the P1 propodus of this species is known, the comparisons with other species of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC417A604B8FAB6A9E9" authorityName="Beurlen" authorityYear="1928" box="[1176,1326,1714,1740]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC417A604B8FAB6A9E9" box="[1176,1326,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Stenodactylina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are limited. 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC4101504D8FBF0A9C9" baseAuthorityName="Bachmayer" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[811,1128,1746,1772]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strambergensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC4101504D8FBF0A9C9" box="[811,1128,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">Stenodactylina strambergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the particularity to have a relatively short propodus. Moreover, the ornamentation of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC410750518FC62A809" baseAuthorityName="Bachmayer" baseAuthorityYear="1959" box="[843,1018,1810,1836]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strambergensis">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC410750518FC62A809" box="[843,1018,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">S. strambergensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is homogeneous – only made of coarse tubercles – contrary to other species, except 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC416290538FAE7A86E" baseAuthorityName="Secretan" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[1303,1407,1842,1868]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC416290538FAE7A86E" box="[1303,1407,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">S. armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C075FFFC410100558FC06A84E" baseAuthorityName="Stenzel" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[814,926,1873,1900]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Stenodactylina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="39" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triglypta">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D075FFFC410100558FC06A84E" box="[814,926,1873,1900]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="62">S. triglypta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
